TARRANT TX-
729 PM CDT FRI MAR 30 2007

...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 800 PM CDT
FOR TARRANT COUNTY...

AT 729 PM CDT...NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE METEOROLOGISTS DETECTED LINE
OF SEVERE THUNDERSTORMS CAPABLE OF PRODUCING PENNY SIZE HAIL...AND
DAMAGING WINDS IN EXCESS OF 60 MPH.  THESE STORMS WERE LOCATED ALONG 
A LINE EXTENDING FROM EAGLE MOUNTAIN TO WEST FORT WORTH TO 
CROWLEY...MOVING EAST AT 30 MPH.

SEVERE THUNDERSTORMS WILL BE NEAR...
  HASLET AND BLUE MOUND BY 735 PM CDT...
  HALTOM CITY AND FOREST HILL BY 740 PM CDT...
  WATAUGA...RICHLAND HILLS...NORTH RICHLAND HILLS AND KELLER BY 745
  PM CDT...
  PANTEGO AND HURST BY 750 PM CDT...

A TORNADO WATCH IS IN EFFECT FOR THE WARNING AREA. SEVERE
THUNDERSTORMS CAN PRODUCE TORNADOES WITH LITTLE OR NO WARNING.

A TORNADO WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 100 AM CDT SATURDAY MORNING
FOR EASTERN TEXAS.

LAT...LON 3297 9748 3259 9747 3268 9704 3298 9702

